<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-20T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/457</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MIN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-20T17:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 22, 12.30
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2342. In reference to my 2308, June 15, 5 p.m. and 2309, June 15, 6
                                p.m. Swedish Government is awaiting written reply from the
                                Associated Governments that the agreement as ratified by Sweden is
                                satisfactory. The Italian Minister has received word from his
                                Government that same is satisfactory but to wait informing the
                                Swedish Government until the other Allied representatives here did
                                the same. The British Minister received word from his Government
                                that the agreement having been signed in England with full powers by
                                their delegates, no further action on their part is necessary after
                                ratification by Swedish Government and has so informed the Swedish
                                Foreign Minister. I am therefore awaiting authority from you
                                regarding this matter and would call to your attention that the
                                Swedish Government has been expecting to hear from me.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MIN1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>